&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CONSULTANT IN HAEMATOLOGY- 10 PA including on call. Less than full time will be considered.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our haematology team is made up of a wide range of enthusiastic and passionate individuals which includes 7 consultants, 3 specialist registrars and 3 clinical nurse specialists and an Advanced Nurse Practitioner providing clinical and laboratory haematology services across the Mid Yorkshire NHS Trust This appointment is a replacement post joining this well-established team. The Trust is an allied teaching hospital and offers the potential for honorary academic positions and sub speciality interests including transfusion. Haematology in-patient care is centralized onto the Pinderfield’s site and operates a British Committee for Standards (BCSH) in Haematology level 3 service; it has JACIE accreditation under the umbrella of the Yorkshire Regional Bone Marrow Transplant programme. Haematology is supported by the large Trust Research Team with dedicated haematology staff who attend the weekly MDT and ward rounds. There are over 20 active haematology trials at present. There are outpatient clinics held on all three hospital sites supported by chemotherapy day units. The Laboratory services have full CPA, HTA and MHRA accreditation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Every one of our 8000 staff at the Mid Yorkshire Hospitals NHS Trust plays a vital role in providing quality care to thousands of people living across Wakefield and North Kirklees each year.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We’re proud that our workforce - our greatest asset - strives for excellence every day in providing care and support to those who use our services. Mid-Yorkshire celebrates excellence and innovation. We have modern, state-of-the-art facilities and provide first class learning and development opportunities. Mid-Yorks is transforming, grounded in our values to care and improve, respecting our patients, our community and our staff, to deliver the highest standards of care.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are a dynamic, innovative and forward-thinking clinician with a passion for your profession and an enthusiasm to be part of a Trust striving to be the best, get in touch to see what a career at Mid-Yorkshire could be like for you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants should possess, or be within 6 months of receiving a CCT at the time of the advisory appointments committee.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The appointment will be on the basis of the new consultant contract laid down by the Hospital Medical and Dental Staff Terms and Conditions of Service and will be remunerated as appropriate on the salary scale £79,860 - £107,668 per annum.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Should applicants be currently or recently employed in a medical capacity the Mid Yorkshire Hospitals NHS Trust reserves the right to request a reference from the Medical Director and/or Responsible Officer of any previous or current employing organisations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information please contact in the first instance Dr Clare Kane, Consultant Haematologist telephone: 01924 816242 and 01924 543834&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Candidates are welcome to visit the department &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
